	   <a name=104844490916136></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104844490916136><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104844490916136>51-55 TS dock People guide</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=104844490916136#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=203298><span id=Sage>Dread Lord Boneklaw</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>33 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 23rd 2:16 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dock A<br><br>Dock A is at -389.92, -1073.89, -5.66. There are 3 mobs on it:<br>Trevor Nalinson – Half Elf Male<br>Brodlan Remdo – Human Male<br>Liteema Agner – Halfling Female<br><br>Dock B<br><br>Dock B is at +150.63, -984.54, +20.60. There are 3 mobs on it:<br>Ellen Daleson – Human Female<br>Edgar Lemoof – Wood Elf Male<br>Rilla Quickeyes – Wood Elf Female<br><br>Dock C (Katta Dock)<br><br>Dock C is at -431. 95, -1731.28, -2436. There are 2 mobs on it:<br>Herald Shelia Gransith – Human Female<br>Brolan Geppal – Half Elf Male<br><br>Katta Entrance<br><br>The Entrance to Katta Castellum is at -107.54, -1879.02, +94.69. There are 2 guards here:<br>Legionnaire Eandalion – Human Male Guard<br>Legionnaire Frankulus – Human Male Guard<br><br>From Dock C, you follow the ramp up to the entrance to Katta Castellum.<br><br>Setup.<br><br>Spell Lineup:<br>1) Drain Soul (Deflux at 54)<br>2) Dooming Darkness<br>3) Invoke Fear<br>4) Splurt<br>5) Lich/Summon Companion<br>6) Bond of Death<br>7) Augment Death/Paralyzing Earth<br>8) Feign Death<br><br>Stand at -535.67, -1151.02, -11.87. Cast pet and have it guard. Invoke Death from 51-53, Minion of Shadows from 53-55. Cast Augment Death on your pet, you will want this on all the time. From this location, the Dock C is east. Docks A and B, as they will be reffered to, are North. You can see Dock A, it will be right next to you, a safe distance away. Keep Dead Man Floating and Arch Shielding up at all times.<br><br>Breaking the Spawn.<br><br>Cast Lich, run across to Dock C, and cast Splurt on Herald Shelia Gransith. Wait till she’s in the water, and run back to your pet. Start spamming Dooming Darkness till she gets in range and it lets you cast. This will give you just enough time to have her snared by the time she is on land and halfway to your pet. Sick the pet on her, step back a little bit, and cast Invoke Fear. Now, there is a timing issue here that you’ll have to work with to get it down to a science. It’s easy enough to figure out with a little practice. <br><br>Once Shelia is dead, target Trevor Nalinson on Dock A and cast Darkness and then Bond of Death, sick pet and Invoke Fear. Once Trevor is dead, run back to Dock C and pull Brolan Geppal repeating the above mentioned process with Shelia on Brolan. Once Brolan is dead, pull Brodlan Remdo, and then Liteema Agner with the same method you used with Trevor. You will alternate Splurt and Bond of Death on the mobs, Splurt one mob, BoD the next. This will make sure that you keep up your hitpoints as you will have Lich on all the time. <br><br>Now that Docks A and C are clear, tell your pet to follow you and run to -14.59, -1027.73, +42.86. Park the pet here and pull Ellen Daleson from Dock B with Dooming Darkness. Fall back to -128.95, -1079.68, -0.67. Cast Bond of Death, sick pet, and Invoke Fear. Continue alternating Splurt and BoD here, pulling Edgar Lemoof next, and then Rilla Quickeyes.<br><br>Now that Dock B is clear, keep pet parked, and run to the Katta Entrance. When you reach -183.77, -1779.16, +44.16, you will be at the bottom of the 3rd ramp down from the Katta Entrance. Cast Summon Companion and tell him to guard immediately or he will run back to the hill by Dock B. Be careful if you have him follow instead of guard because if he walks over the edge of the ramps to Katta he will poof. Now that the pet is guarded, face east towards the wall. You will see the ramp goes up, on either side of the ramp are ledges that frame the ramp. Stand on the right ledge and walk slowly up the ramp until you see Legionnaire Eandalion aggro. Then step back to the pet. This is how you can pull the guards single. This does not always work, but it works a lot of the time. If you get them together, simply Fear one and then Dark/Fear/Splurt or Bod, the other and let your pet kill it. You could also Root one but it can be a pain. When Fear wears off the guard will come running back to you, so it’s no big deal. Once Eandalion is down, assuming you got him single, just sick your pet on Frankulus and Dark/Fear/DoT him. <br><br>Once all 10 mobs are dead, click Lich off and run back to -535.67, -1151.02, -11.87. You will have a few minutes to rest up for the next round, maybe 3-5 minutes. Once Herald Shelia Gransith repops, start all over again. This is good XP all the way to 55, it slows down a bit at 54, but you’ll feel better if you just grind out 54. Once you’re 55, you can move on to Katta Guards (Outside Graveyard).<br><br>Notes:<br><br>All of this is up debate due to personal style. My way is an exact science that works fast, efficient and every time. You will not get adds at 51 except for when pulling the guards unless you screw up and let your pet and the mob it’s killing get to close to another mob. This only happened to me once. <br><br>If something happens, it’s taking too long to kill a mob, or a mob actually getd physical with you and you lose more health than normal, just Drain Soul/Deflux to give yourself a boost.<br><br>The only loot is a very rare Fishing Pole which is the same one that you can buy at most Fishing Vendors across EverQuest.<br><br>At level 55 all of the Mobs will be Light Blue, they will all be Dark Blue before this level.<br><br>This is also decent AAXP even at 55 when everything is Light Blue. AAXP sucks pre-60, so when I say decent, I mean decent AAXP for levels 51-55....Thank you Maghrsite :)<br><br>Hope this posted guide will help you out...however...As of the LOY expansion the TS zone is a bit Hacked and not that safe til they fix it....just word of warning to you....Da Bone.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Mar 23 13:55:45 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Boneklaw Von`Torment<br>I live in the shadows, I'm hated & rejected,I command the dead,I control disease,I alter blood,I give life & I take it away, I'm the culmination of all you fear,I am Necromancer</td></tr>
