	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wow,I guess this is like getting a Corvette Stick shift and not knowing how to drive.You can look at it and know its powerful,but frustrated you cant take her for a spin....<br><br>(your point #4)<br>Thoughts on PVP(since your on a pvp server its PvP first you worry about then PvE- &quot;enviroment&quot;)<br><br>First of all you have truly been handed a very powerful killing machine.I can also say that someone did most of the painful levels for you as a Necro really begins to shine Post 49+.Depending upon the server your on,limits your worries greatly concerning other classes.<br><br> Rallos Zek is PVP anytime any where from anyone.All classes are at or can be at war with one another.The loot rules are tough too.If your killed by another player they can take one of your items on your person...say goodbye to a 10K robe? Sorry Rallos isnt for me guys.<br><br> Vallon Zek and Tallon Zek is PVP teams ...good fun. The thing is your DE, so if your on one of these your enemies are anything other than Ogres Trolls Darkelfs and Iksar...loot rules are coin only...Bank often and dont carry tons of cash.Other races can be necros,so dont be surprised if your most deadly spells in your book start landing on you...I hate fighting other necros,often times you both will die.<br><br> Sullon Zek.. oh boy you gotta be tough or crazy to play here(I am both!)...Alignment based...Goods vs Neutrals vs Evils...Tough rule set. Anyone over level 6 is fair game.A level 65 can attack and kill a level 7.Loot is coin only though and No exp loss if killed by someone higher than 5 levels above you.The good thing? All necros are evil so you never have to face another necro in a fight :)<br><br>THE single biggest class to fear is Rangers with AM3(Arch Mastery 3).I would never say run except here.Gate if you live long enough to do so.The damage 3 arrows can do from a distance you can't even cast a spell to is enough to exceed your hit point total.The second worse class to face is your own.Necro's versus Necro's....they got what you got.Like USA and Russia unleashing Nukes at each other.Get the picture ?<br><br>(your point #2)<br>Leveling well I tried to cover that in my recent post 1-65 My life as a necro please read for what and how I did my levels.<br><br>(your point #3)<br>Grouping really is a good idea on PvP servers.Find a good guild and join it.Most hard XPing necro's are always low on health due to liching etc.The newer spells that are coming along all seem to be group orientated.This is by no accident, these are in my opnion, designed to make a necro much more desired in group play.Besides a solo necro in the middle of a fight with a mob while low on health is a easy kill for someone.Dont think they will let you finish your kill med to full health and mana then &quot;play&quot; hehe.At 59-60+ bah the exp is so good on the planes that you cant out-xp a good group.<br><br>(your point #1)<br>This is the hardest one of all, you see the climb to greatness for the necro isnt just about levels.Its the how to do what and the when to do what that makes this class so powerful.<br><br>I would suggest you print a listing of all the necro's spells and study each one.Even the early ones to understand what each spell does and how it does it, how long it takes and what its based on(fire disease,cold,poison)I have linked a great site for your spells to simply print them off here. <br><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Necromancer" target=_new>http://eq.crgaming.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Necromancer</a><br><br>Secondly this is a great site for necromancers of any level.Read read read read read.It covers many subjects including pet control,hunting areas,spell information, AA information, etc..its a necromancer's dream site for information.<br><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/default.asp" target=_new>http://necro.eqclasses.com/forum/default.asp</a><br><br>Lastly I simply just couldnt survive unless I had luclin and Planes of Power.You need those two expansions and I would rate them very highly.I have Legacy now also.The Planes of Power open up unreal xp spots for you in a group and honestly you almost have to have them for most guilds wont have you if you dont....<br><br>Closing thought, there is so much to say about a necro that I could not possibly cover all I would and need to say.I simply hope that I can inspire you to learn as much as possible about this treasure you have been given.Its a awsome class,its feared in PvP, and its tough to master.But ..your a Master of the Undead now and you can handle anything ...good luck to you Da'Bone<br>&nbsp;<br>Boneklaw Von`Torment<br>I live in the shadows, I'm hated & rejected,I command the dead,I control disease,I alter blood,I give life & I take it away, I'm the culmination of all you fear,I am Necromancer</td></tr>
